rComments: Due to the pandemic, this class was offered online and I haven't learned a thing. This professor gives absolutely no guidance on projects, then complains when it wasn't "what she had in mind". Also she explains nothing in class apart from reading the slides. I didn't take this class to teach myself. My advice? Avoid her.

The midterm is disappointed. It examined many things that you will not notice. And the prof. sometimes seems like not sure about the answer of your questions. And the grade of presentation is low. Be careful to choose this class. There will be midterm, final, presentations, report, quiz in this lecture. And the professor has accent .

Dr. Baranova is a very good professor, she is clear and helpful. Her notes are all you need to know for the midterm. The final is more difficult, because you come in with a mentality of it going to be tough and panic. If you concentrate, you will do well. Only reason I got a B+, is because I forgot to do a whole number on the final.

Had her for heat tranfer and for thermodynamics. She's alright. Her printable notes are easy enough to follow and her examples are often useful, but her in class explanations are more often than not quite confusing. Midterm is usually easy, but final exam is much more difficult.
